Cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT)
Last Update: August 21, 2025; Next update: 2028.
Cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT) is one of the most common and best studied forms of
psychotherapy. It is a combination of two therapeutic approaches, known as cognitive
therapy and behavioral therapy.
The exact treatment approaches used will depend on the illness or problem to be treated.
But the basic idea behind the therapy is always the same: What we think, how we behave,
and how other people make us feel are all closely related – and they all affect our
wellbeing.
--------------------------------------------------

