Source: C:\capstone\SafeSpaceAI\SafeSpaceAI\dataIngestion\docs\Cognitive behavioral therapy.txt
Length: 761 characters
Content:
Go to:
What is cognitive therapy?
The term cognitive comes from the Latin "cognoscere," meaning "to recognize." Cognitive
therapy is about forming a clear idea of your own thoughts, attitudes and expectations. The
goal is to recognize and change false and distressing beliefs. It is often not only everyday
circumstances or particular situations themselves that cause problems, but the
exaggerated importance that we attach to them, too.
One example of a distressing thought pattern is over-generalization: This involves creating a
universal rule from one bad experience and applying it to similar situations. Another
distressing way of thinking is known as “catastrophizing”: An unsettling event leads you to
start worrying about a much worse looming disaster.
--------------------------------------------------

